The paper discusses a new approach to reinforcement learning that transforms it into a form of supervised learning, which is a topic commonly studied in the machine learning community (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of this approach in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. Additionally, the paper touches on the use of computational functions and algorithms (cs.AI) to achieve high rewards or other goals. Finally, the paper discusses the concept of imitation learning, which is a topic commonly studied in the control systems community (cs.SY).
